    <with|font-series|bold|Automated Theorem Proving:> Automated theorem
    proving is the proving of mathematical theorems by a computer program. A
    simpler, but related problem is proof verification, where an existing
    proof for a theorem is certified valid. For this, it is generally
    required that each individual proof step can be verified by a computer
    program.

    <\itemize-dot>
      <item>Own Research: Development of the automated higher-order theorem
      prover LEO and its integration with state-of-the-art first-order
      theorem provers (e.g. Vampire) based on the multi-agent architecture
      OANTS (see below).

